President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New Mexico due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance, for all areas in New Mexico impacted by COVID-19. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has named George A. Robinson as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and warranted by further assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.